**Event Title:** SAINTCON Family Night

**Overview:**
- The SAINTCON Family Night Event is designed for conference attendees to bring their families to experience activities and discussions centered around cyber-security and technology.
- The event emphasizes creativity, critical-thinking, and imagination among participants.

**Activities Planned:**
- Kid Talks
- CTF (Capture The Flag) – participants are encouraged to bring devices
- Cipher Challenge
- Bristle Bots
- Circuit Building
- Rocket Building
- Soldering Station
- Lego Racetrack
- Fingerprint Lifting
- Keyboard Art
- Scavenger Hunt
- Tinfoil Hats
- Lockpicking

**Presentations:**
- Children and youth will present on STEM topics they have learned. Families are encouraged to participate and possibly share their own presentations.

**Target Audience:**
- Geared towards family members of SAINTCON attendees aged 4-16, although all family members are welcome.

**Registration Information:**
- Registration for family members (participants) begins on **August 17, 2024**.
- Limited to **500 participants**; early registration is recommended.
- Cost: **$12 per participant**, which includes an event bag with supplies.
- All children must be accompanied by at least one adult with a SAINTCON Conference badge.
  
**Event Details:**
- **Date:** Thursday, **October 24, 2024**
- **Time:** 6:00 PM - 8:30 PM

**Event Bag Contents:**
- Bag provided by the Family Night Event Sponsor, Compunet
- Family Night MiniBadge
- Hacker Stickers
- Invitation to SAINTCON Minecraft™ Server
- Scavenger Hunt details, maps, and other information
- Family Night T-shirt (limited to first 500 registrations)

**Volunteers:**
- SAINTCON attendees are invited to volunteer for the event.

**Registration Link:** [Register for Family Night Event](http://register.saintcon.org/familynight) 

This event aims to make the world of cyber-security accessible and engaging for families, fostering interest in STEM and technology from a young age.